21/12/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Kosovo Prime Minister Ramush Haradinaj met on Monday (20 December) with co-ordinators of the eight working groups for implementation of international standards in Kosovo.
They discussed upcoming activities and agreed that the task forces would prepare and present operational plans within a week.
No Serb representatives participated.
In other news Monday, Kosovo Serb leaders urged Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica to accept an invitation for talks on decentralisation and security, reportedly extended by UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen.
They say that launching talks between UNMIK and Belgrade could lead to their eventual participation in provincial institutions.
(Politika - 21/12/04;
KosovaLive, Beta, B92, Tanjug - 20/12/04)
